cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for remote sensing image pansharpening. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also explores architectural and training variations to the baseline CNN, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of target-adaptive usage modality and the off-the-shelf software tool may also suggest a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia), respectively. Finally, the remote sensing aspect of the paper may suggest a possible fit with cs.GR (Graphics).
